Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.38,0:00:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever asked, “How long?”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.45,0:00:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re enduring
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.62,0:00:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,some challenging circumstance right now
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.59,0:00:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,—perhaps old age, a serious illness,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.69,0:00:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or some other pressure—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.50,0:00:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,such a question is very understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.87,0:00:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps you’re in the position\Nof giving assistance
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.94,0:00:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to encourage a family member\Nor someone in the congregation 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.24,0:00:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,who’s going through\Na very difficult time right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.04,0:00:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and perhaps you’ve wondered\Nabout the same question: ‘How long?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.38,0:00:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How long do we all\Nhave to endure all of this?’
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.75,0:00:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Asking that question puts us in good company.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.46,0:00:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,To cite one example, at Psalm 13:1, 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.63,0:00:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,King David asked the question, “How long?”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.46,0:00:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,four times in quick succession.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.87,0:00:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you recall: “How long, O Jehovah,\Nwill you forget me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.17,0:00:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“Forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.47,0:00:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“How long will you hide your face from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.34,0:01:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“How long will I have anxious concern,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.08,0:01:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“with grief in my heart each day?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.71,0:01:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How long will my enemy triumph over me?”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.52,0:01:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,David was a human—a real person
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.79,0:01:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with real problems and real feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.33,0:01:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Habakkuk was another human just like us
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.66,0:01:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,who was plagued with questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.63,0:01:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and he asked the same: “How long?”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.20,0:01:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How Jehovah responded to Habakkuk
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.34,0:01:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,can strengthen our resolve to wait
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.21,0:01:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,just a little while longer 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.61,0:01:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,on Jehovah, to wait patiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.38,0:01:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Please open your Bible with me
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.38,0:01:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to Habakkuk chapter 1,\Nand let’s read verses 2 and 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.99,0:01:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And notice the succession
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.22,0:01:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of six emotion-filled questions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.06,0:01:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,—Habakkuk 1:2, 3:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.00,0:01:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“How long, O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.30,0:02:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“must I cry for help, but you do not hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.27,0:02:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“How long must I ask for help from violence,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.31,0:02:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“but you do not intervene?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.78,0:02:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why do you make me witness wrongdoing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.41,0:02:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“And why do you tolerate oppression?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.92,0:02:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“Why are destruction and violence before me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.95,0:02:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And why do quarreling and conflict abound?”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.86,0:02:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think those were good questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.56,0:02:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They were.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.83,0:02:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Like us, Habakkuk\Nwas living in a very difficult time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.86,0:02:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Violence, oppression, injustice were rampant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.20,0:02:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Habakkuk was deeply distressed
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.21,0:02:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,by the circumstances\Nthat he was experiencing, that he was seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.34,0:02:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, he wanted to know\Nhow long it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.88,0:02:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,before Jehovah fulfilled\Nthe promise he had already given
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.72,0:02:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring judgment\Nagainst that wicked system of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But how Jehovah responded\Nto his faithful prophet’s questions
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.69,0:02:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,really can strengthen\Nour confidence in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice in chapter 2 and verse 3,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.40,0:03:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,though not obligated to answer,\Nwhat did Jehovah tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.10,0:03:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Habakkuk 2:3:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.67,0:03:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“For the vision\Nis yet for its appointed time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.74,0:03:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“and it is rushing toward its end,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“and it will not lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.45,0:03:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Even if it should delay,\Nkeep in expectation of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.42,0:03:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“For it will without fail come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.59,0:03:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It will not be late!”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.43,0:03:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful reassurance from Jehovah,\Nwouldn’t you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.16,0:03:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Analyze those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.16,0:03:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice first that Jehovah assured Habakkuk
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.33,0:03:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that divine judgment was coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.11,0:03:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah had not changed his stated purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.88,0:03:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Jehovah added that there was 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.88,0:03:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,an “appointed [or fixed] time”\Nfor that judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.48,0:03:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In effect, Jehovah was telling Habakkuk,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Habakkuk, the day of judgment\Nis on my calendar.’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.19,0:04:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah then added more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that the judgment was “rushing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.29,0:04:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,toward its end,” or its fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.53,0:04:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“It [would] not lie.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a result of thinking and meditating\Non those assurances,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.33,0:04:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Habakkuk had no reason to be impatient\Nor to give way to despair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.81,0:04:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, instead of criticizing Habakkuk
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.94,0:04:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,for those very sincere,\Nvery poignant questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.71,0:04:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah encouraged Habakkuk:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.22,0:04:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“Keep in expectation of it!”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.69,0:04:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait eagerly for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.69,0:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“It will not be late!”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.12,0:04:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know,\Nit’s one thing to receive encouragement,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.53,0:04:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but I’m sure you’d agree\Nthat it’s another thing to fully accept it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.06,0:04:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to take it to heart and be nourished at heart\Nby such encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.63,0:04:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Habakkuk\Ntake Jehovah’s response to heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.77,0:04:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it encourage him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.11,0:04:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, cast your eyes\Nto chapter 2 and verse 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.88,0:04:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’ll notice\Nthat Habakkuk’s communication with Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:05:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,did, in fact, calm his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He resolved to keep waiting confidently
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.65,0:05:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and patiently on Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, in chapter 3 and verse 16,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.29,0:05:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Habakkuk repeated his resolve when he said
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that he would\N“quietly wait” for Jehovah’s day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.07,0:05:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what does all of this have to do\Nwith you and with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we live at a time when Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.54,0:05:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,has also appointed a fixed day of judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.84,0:05:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nearly 2,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the Father already knew\Nwhen the end would come, according to Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.88,0:05:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,At Matthew 24:36,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.55,0:05:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,what had Jehovah already established?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.89,0:05:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,A “day and hour.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.59,0:05:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So that means that the day\Nthat you and I eagerly anticipate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is on Jehovah’s calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.73,0:05:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been there for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.83,0:05:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It will come on time, at the right time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.44,0:05:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,at a time that Jehovah\Nknows to be the best time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And isn’t that what we would expect\Nof our best Friend, Jehovah God;
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.51,0:06:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of love; the Great Timekeeper;\N“the King of eternity”?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.05,0:06:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditating on the fact\Nthat the day and hour is established 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.79,0:06:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,helps us renew our resolve
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.16,0:06:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep waiting patiently on Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.63,0:06:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if the day seems to be delaying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Interestingly, there at Habakkuk 2:3,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.07,0:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah himself\Nbrought up the subject of a delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.17,0:06:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Jehovah who said:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.27,0:06:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“Even if it should delay,\Nkeep in expectation of it!”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how could the end come on time\Nand yet be delayed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.68,0:06:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, consider the situation\Nback in Habakkuk’s day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.45,0:06:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about 100 years earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.56,0:06:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that the prophet Isaiah had foretold
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.79,0:06:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah would use Babylon\Nto bring a day of judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.43,0:06:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you or I were in Habakkuk’s sandals,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.70,0:06:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,how might we have felt?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.03,0:07:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,From our point of view\Nenduring that wicked system of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.97,0:07:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it may have well seemed\Nthat the day of Jehovah was delaying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.08,0:07:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And if Habakkuk felt that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.74,0:07:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,then Jehovah’s assurances\Nsurely comforted him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.15,0:07:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, we noticed that Jehovah\Ndidn’t criticize him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.68,0:07:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for asking, How long? How long? twice 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.29,0:07:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and, Why? four times.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.55,0:07:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.42,0:07:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah took into consideration
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.23,0:07:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the pain of heart of his friend\Nand then reassured him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.13,0:07:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you know what happened 20 years later?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.93,0:07:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s words were fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.37,0:07:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Jerusalem was destroyed in 607 B.C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So had there really been a delay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.28,0:07:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That delay was only a perceived one
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.91,0:07:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the mind of Habakkuk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you and I can look back
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.45,0:07:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,through the book of history\Nand see the bigger picture, 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.59,0:07:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,one that Habakkuk\Nsimply could not see fully in his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.06,0:08:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And what do we see now\Nabout that day of judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.80,0:08:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in 607 B.C.E.?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.27,0:08:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like a piece\Nin a very detailed but beautiful puzzle,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the destruction of Jerusalem\Ncame right on time
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.41,0:08:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—at the perfect time—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.71,0:08:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because that was a pivotal date\Nin the fulfillment of other Bible prophecies,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.38,0:08:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,prophecies that have to do\Nwith our day during the last days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.96,0:08:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So while Habakkuk\Nmay have thought that there was a delay,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.89,0:08:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah knew better.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.76,0:08:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the reminder\Nthat nourishes our heart this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.53,0:08:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything linked to Jehovah’s grand purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.07,0:08:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,has always been and will always be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.57,0:08:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in the perfect control\Nof the Great Timekeeper, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.65,0:08:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In summary, we could conclude\Nfrom our Morning Worship program today
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.32,0:08:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that Habakkuk’s experience\Nteaches us valuable lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.72,0:09:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,One, Jehovah is not indifferent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to the suffering and the emotional distress\Nof his servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.26,0:09:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So are you in some emotional distress
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.80,0:09:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or assisting someone else who is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.60,0:09:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t be afraid\Nto keep pouring out your heart to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.71,0:09:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,helping others to do so,\Neven repeatedly if needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.95,0:09:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Habakkuk,\Nwait patiently for the answers,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.58,0:09:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the reassurance that Jehovah will provide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.92,0:09:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember this too about the salvation\Nthat Jehovah has foretold:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.69,0:09:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,His salvation for his people\Nis not a temporary solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not a bandage on a wound.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.20,0:09:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,His solution will completely resolve
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.77,0:09:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,any and all trials we may be experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.27,0:09:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Once they’re gone, they’re gone for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.24,0:09:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So how reassuring it is—isn’t it?—to know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.48,0:09:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that today we are one day closer
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:10:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to the fixed day\Nthat’s on Jehovah’s calendar!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.82,0:10:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s judgments\Nby means of his Kingdom will not be late.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.45,0:00:04.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバ いつまでですか」
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.59,0:00:08.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう尋ねずにはいられなかったことが\Nあるかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.63,0:00:12.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,高齢や重い病気や\N他の難しい問題のために
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.50,0:00:15.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,そう尋ねたくなるのも無理はありません
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.00,0:00:20.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいはあなたは とても難しい状況に\N置かれている家族や
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.77,0:00:23.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,会衆の仲間を援助していて
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.37,0:00:26.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,力になりたいと思っているかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.14,0:00:30.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,そしてやはり こう尋ねたくなります
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.15,0:00:35.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバ 私たちはいつまで\N忍耐しなければいけないのですか」
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.65,0:00:40.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,こういう質問をしたのは\Nハバククだけではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.62,0:00:44.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,例えば 詩編 13:1, 2で
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.13,0:00:49.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデ王は 矢継ぎ早に4回\N「いつまで」と尋ねています
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.83,0:00:55.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります 「エホバ いつまで私を\N忘れているのですか 永遠にですか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.61,0:00:57.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまで顔を隠すのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.01,0:01:03.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまで私は思い悩み 毎日悲しみに\N暮れなければならないのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.85,0:01:07.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつまで敵は勝利するのですか」
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.55,0:01:12.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,ダビデは私たちと同じような\N感情を持つ人間でした
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.42,0:01:15.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,さまざまな問題も抱えていました
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.23,0:01:21.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククも私たちと同じように\N弱さを持つ人間でした
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.60,0:01:26.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして「いつまでですか」と尋ねました
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.17,0:01:29.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがハバククに\Nどう答えたかを考えると
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.71,0:01:33.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも もう少しエホバを待とう
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.08,0:01:37.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,辛抱強く待とうという決意が強まります
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.78,0:01:40.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご一緒にハバクク 1章を開いて
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.58,0:01:43.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,2, 3節を読んでみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.02,0:01:47.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククは次から次へと質問をして
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.09,0:01:50.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバに切実な気持ちを伝えます
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.16,0:01:55.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,「エホバ 私はいつまで助けを求めて\N叫ばなければならないのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.20,0:01:57.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは聞いてくださらないのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.57,0:02:02.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,私はいつまで暴力からの救出を\N願わなければならないのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.34,0:02:05.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは介入してくださらないのですか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.07,0:02:08.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,私に悪事を見させるのはどうしてですか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.21,0:02:11.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,圧制を見過ごしておられるのは\Nどうしてですか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:14.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,私の前に破壊や暴力があるのはなぜですか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.95,0:02:18.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,口論や争いがあまりにも多いのは\Nなぜですか」
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:22.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,皆さんも同じように感じますか
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.56,0:02:28.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっとそうでしょう ハバククは今と\N同じように 大変な時に生活していました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.26,0:02:32.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,暴力や圧制や不正が広く見られていました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.07,0:02:36.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククはそうした状況を見たり\N経験したりして
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.57,0:02:39.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ひどく心を乱されていました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:41.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,それでハバククは
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.28,0:02:46.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがいつ約束を果たしてくださるのか\N知りたいと思っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.72,0:02:50.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,悪い人たちを処罰するという約束です
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:55.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,では エホバがハバククの質問に\Nどう答えたかに注目しましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.96,0:02:59.60,Default2,,0,0,0,,きっとエホバへの信頼が\N強まることでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.63,0:03:02.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバクク 2:3をご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:07.04,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバには答える義務は\Nありませんでしたが こう言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.07,0:03:09.81,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバクク 2:3
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.87,0:03:13.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,「この幻は定められた時のためのもので
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.91,0:03:16.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,終わりに向かって急いでおり
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.41,0:03:18.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,偽りではない
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.48,0:03:22.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,たとえ遅れるとしても 待ち続けよ
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.59,0:03:25.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,必ずその通りになるからである
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.86,0:03:28.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,遅くなることはない！」
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.46,0:03:33.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククはこの言葉を聞いて\N安心したことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.46,0:03:35.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,内容を見てみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.53,0:03:37.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,まずエホバはハバククに
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.53,0:03:41.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,処罰が必ず下されることを保証しました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.17,0:03:45.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは考えを変えてはいませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.98,0:03:51.15,Default2,,0,0,0,,「定められた時」に処罰が\N下されることを明らかにしました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.51,0:03:54.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはいわばこう言っていました
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.05,0:03:58.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,「ハバクク 処罰の日は\N私のカレンダーに書いてある」
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.22,0:04:01.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらにこう言いました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.22,0:04:05.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,処罰は 「終わり［または実現］に\N向かって急いで」いる
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.36,0:04:07.46,Default2,,0,0,0,,「偽りではない」
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:11.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククはこのような保証の言葉を\N思い巡らしました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.37,0:04:16.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして諦めたり 絶望したり\Nすべきではないことを理解しました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.91,0:04:21.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,このように 切実にエホバに訴え\N質問したハバククを
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.14,0:04:23.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは批判したりしませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:26.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,むしろ こう言って励ましました
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.48,0:04:30.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,「待ち続けよ ［心から待ち望め］
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.22,0:04:32.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,遅くなることはない」
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.16,0:04:37.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,励ましの言葉をただ聞くのは\N簡単なことです
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:41.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもそれを心から受け入れて\N自分のものにするのは
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.97,0:04:44.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,それほど簡単なことではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.93,0:04:47.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククはどうだったでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.04,0:04:51.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの言葉を受け入れて\N力づけられたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:54.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバクク 2:1をご覧ください
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.18,0:04:58.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,この聖句にある通り\Nハバククはエホバと話すことで
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.15,0:05:01.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,穏やかな気持ちになることができました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.68,0:05:06.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククはエホバを信じて\N辛抱強く待つことにしました
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:12.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,3:16でもハバククは\Nその決意を言い表しています
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.13,0:05:17.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,「私は［エホバ］の日を\N静かに待ちます」と言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:20.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,では私たちはどうでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:24.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちも裁きの日を迎えようとしています
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.94,0:05:27.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはその日を定めています
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.98,0:05:30.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは2000年近く前から
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.48,0:05:34.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,この体制を終わらせる時を決めています
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.08,0:05:38.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスがマタイ 24:36で\N言ったように
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.05,0:05:41.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは「日と時刻」を定めています
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.66,0:05:45.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ですから 私たちが\N待ち望んでいるその日は
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.43,0:05:48.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,すでにエホバのカレンダーに\N記されています
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.93,0:05:54.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,ずっと前からです その日は予定通りに\N間違いなくやってきます
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.27,0:05:58.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはベストなタイミングで\N行動してくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:00.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちの親友であり
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.01,0:06:04.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,愛の神であり 時間を守る方であり
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.48,0:06:07.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,「永遠の王」だからです
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.18,0:06:10.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,日と時刻が決まっていることを考えると
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.69,0:06:16.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの日をこれからも辛抱強く待とう\Nという決意が強まります
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.29,0:06:20.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもその日が遅れているように思いますか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.46,0:06:24.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,興味深いことに\Nハバクク 2:3を見ると
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.47,0:06:28.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバご自身がその点を取り上げています
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:30.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバはこう言っています
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:34.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,「たとえ遅れるとしても 待ち続けよ」
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.51,0:06:39.12,Default2,,0,0,0,,予定通りに来るはずの日が遅れるとは\Nどういうことでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.72,0:06:43.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククの時代のことを考えてみましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.52,0:06:46.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,その100年ほど前 預言者イザヤは
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:51.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバがバビロンを用いて\N裁きを行うと予告しました
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.66,0:06:54.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,もし私たちがハバククだったら
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.60,0:06:56.94,Default2,,0,0,0,,どう感じたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.13,0:06:59.20,Default2,,0,0,0,,当時は大変な時代でした
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.24,0:07:01.34,Default2,,0,0,0,,そういう中で生活していたら
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:05.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの日が遅れていると\N感じたかもしれません
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.91,0:07:07.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,いずれにしてもハバククは
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.91,0:07:11.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの言葉を聞いて\N安心したことでしょう
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.21,0:07:14.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククは 「いつまで」と2回
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.08,0:07:18.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,「どうして」と2回\N「なぜ」と2回尋ねました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.52,0:07:21.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,でもエホバはハバククを責めたりせず
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.32,0:07:26.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,友であるハバククの心の痛みを\N理解し 安心させました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.10,0:07:31.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうなったでしょうか\N20年後 エホバの言葉は実現しました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.57,0:07:36.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,エルサレムは紀元前607年に\N滅ぼされました
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.11,0:07:39.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,その日は遅れていたのでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.14,0:07:41.14,Default2,,0,0,0,,そうではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.14,0:07:44.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,その裁きの日は ハバククにとって
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.01,0:07:48.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,遅れているように思えただけです
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:52.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,もちろん私たちは\N実際に起きた出来事を知っているので
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.42,0:07:54.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,俯瞰的に考えることができますが
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:08:00.03,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククは裁きの日がいつ来るかを\N正確には知りませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.06,0:08:05.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,では私たちは 紀元前607年について\Nどんなことを知っているでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.40,0:08:09.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,ジグソーパズルは最後のピースが\Nはまると全体像が分かります
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:14.71,Default2,,0,0,0,,同様にエルサレムの滅びが\N完璧なタイミングで来ることによって
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.74,0:08:17.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,全体像が明らかになりました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.15,0:08:20.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,そのタイミングは\N他の聖書預言とも関連しています
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:25.39,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちの時代\N今の終わりの時代に関する預言です
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.02,0:08:29.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククは遅れているように\N感じたかもしれませんが
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.63,0:08:32.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際はそうではありませんでした
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.00,0:08:36.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日はどんなことを学ぶことが\Nできたでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.57,0:08:40.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは時間を守る方です
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.27,0:08:44.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,ご自分が当初考えていた\N壮大な事柄を成し遂げるため
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.44,0:08:47.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,着々と物事を進めてこられました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:49.58,Default2,,0,0,0,,これからもそうされます
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:53.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日の朝の崇拝では\Nハバククに注目しました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.95,0:08:58.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバとハバククのやりとりから\N大切なことを学べました
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.59,0:09:04.83,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つには エホバはご自分に仕える\N人たちの苦しみや心の痛みを
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.83,0:09:08.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,よく分かってくれているということです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.43,0:09:11.47,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなたは心の痛みを抱えていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.50,0:09:14.64,Default2,,0,0,0,,あるいはそういう人を助けていますか
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.67,0:09:17.87,Default2,,0,0,0,,遠慮なくエホバに\N気持ちを打ち明けてください
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.91,0:09:22.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,何度でも祈れます\N仲間にもそうするよう勧めてください
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.01,0:09:26.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,思いやり深いエホバが与えてくれる答えを
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.18,0:09:29.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,ハバククのように辛抱強く待ちましょう
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.99,0:09:34.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバは私たちをどのように救うと\N約束しているでしょうか
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.69,0:09:38.79,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの救いは\N一時的な解決策ではありません
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.83,0:09:42.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,ばんそうこうを貼るような\Nものではないのです
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.27,0:09:45.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,私たちが経験している全ての問題を
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.57,0:09:48.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,完全に解決してくださいます
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.20,0:09:51.80,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう二度と悩まされることはありません
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.31,0:09:55.31,Default2,,0,0,0,,うれしいことに 1日を終えるたびに
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.34,0:10:00.78,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバのカレンダーに記されている日に\Nまた1日近づいたことになります
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.82,0:10:06.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバが王国によって裁きを下す日は\N遅れることはないのです
